name: grilled chicken with tomato salsa & avocado salad
instructions:
1. Mince garlic and place in a small bowl. 

2. Add lemon peel, chili powder, olive oil, kosher salt and black pepper. 

3. Rub mixture liberally over chicken breasts. 

4. Grill over flame turning as meat browns. Cook through (165 degrees F).

5. To make tomato salsa, dice roma tomatoes, green bell pepper, and red onion. 

6. Combine in small bowl, add cilantro leaves, and season with salt and pepper to taste.

7. To make the avocado salad, tear lettuce into bite sized pieces and top with sliced avocado. Drizzle with olive oil.

8. To serve, spoon tomato salsa over cooked chicken and serve with avocado salad.
